metadata.editComments:
Here is a verse for another fun rocking tune by Eddie Money.  This song always always got bodies moving filling the dance floor when playing this as a cover band.  The driving drum beat and volume swell of the guitar to full blast really starts the tune off with a punch.  What's cool about this song is how Eddie Money start singing AFTER the first down beat of each lyric line.  Play the song and listen closely for the following notes.  
Lyric lines 1, 3 and 4 start AFTER strong beat 1 on the and of 1. 
Lyric line 2 starts AFTER strong beat 1 on weak beat 2. 
Think of a favorite song and analyze when the lyric starts in reference to the downbeat like I did.  If you are not already aware of this basic concept then you may find this information very helpful. Start analyzing songs that you really like and write down on what beat the lyric line starts. You may find that the most popular songs strike a perfect balance of starting lyric lines Before, On and After the downbeat.
